narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Although it comes under the guise of an "intro to academic writing", English 114 may foster in you a strong dislike for academic writing. It is not as easy as it may appear; in fact, it is extremely difficult to succeed. You will, however learn a few useful skills and, if you're lucky, develop a thick skin when it comes to criticisms of your writing.
I would recommend it to students who wish to learn about an interesting subject matter and improve their writing abilities
I would not recommend this particular section of English 114. Take the course if you need a writing credit. The grading seemed arbitrary and the course work was not engaging.

I would probably be indifferent when speaking to another student about the course. I would say that if they are interested in writing and improving their writing skills to take english 114 but I would most likely tell them to not take my section. This is mainly due to the readings and structure of the course.
